# Context Template For AI Suggestions

Copy this file to a selectable category folder as `context.txt` only after replacing every placeholder with reviewed category-specific content.

## Category Summary
Describe the TS category, typical customer problem, target plant or process area, and the usual business outcome.

## Standard Scope Patterns
List common in-scope activities, deliverables, engineering tasks, commissioning tasks, and support boundaries.

## Key Components And Integrations
List expected systems, hardware, software, interfaces, protocols, data sources, data consumers, and third-party dependencies.

## Technical Architecture Notes
Summarize common architecture patterns, deployment topology, network zones, server/client roles, data flow, and redundancy expectations.

## Assumptions And Dependencies
List customer prerequisites, site readiness dependencies, input data assumptions, infrastructure expectations, access requirements, and approval dependencies.

## Delivery And Gantt Guidance
Describe typical project phases, sequence, durations in weeks, milestones, and dependencies that should guide Gantt suggestions.

## Section-Specific Guidance
Add concise guidance for TS sections that need category-specific wording, such as executive summary, overview, scope, exclusions, cybersecurity, training, FAT, and support.

## Preferred Terminology
List preferred names, abbreviations, product names, and phrasing conventions. Include terms that should stay consistent across suggestions.

## Avoid Or Verify
List claims the AI should not assume, customer-specific items that must be verified, risky commitments, and details that require SME confirmation.
